Serbia’s Ruling Party Mulls Early Vote in December, Danas Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-03-31T08:41:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/serbia-s-ruling-party-mulls-early-vote-in-december-danas-says.html
Serbia’s ruling  Democratic Party 
may accept opposition demands for early elections and set a vote
for Dec. 18 after an expected European Union approval of the
country as a candidate for membership,  Danas  newspaper reported,
citing party sources it did not name.  The Democrats want the vote to take place soon after the
 European Council ’s decision expected in October and after  Fiat
SpA (F) ’s unit in Serbia starts producing two new models in November
as the events should boost the party’s popularity, the report
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  